            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e108">Rubrica 5</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De militia et officio et laudibus militum et sacramento eorum</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e114">
              De militia 
              <lb ed="#K" n="78"/>et officio et laudibus mili<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tum 
              et sacramento eorum. Rubrica. 5.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e121">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e118">UEgetius de re militari libro 2 titulo 5.</ref> 
              <lb ed="#K"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e127">Iurant milites omnia se stre<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>nue 
              facturos que preceperit imperator 
                  <pb ed="#K" n="211-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#K" n="a"/>
              <lb ed="#K" n="1"/>nunquam deserturos militiam: nec 
              <lb ed="#K"/>mortem recusaturos pro republica.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e139"> 
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e137">18. libro.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e141">In congruum videretur impera<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>toris
              militem qui veste et anno<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>na 
              publica pasceretur vtilitatibus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vacare puatis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e150"> 
                <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e150">23 libro et penultimo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e152">Mi<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>les 
                sacramento lectus ab exercitio ar<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>morum 
                vel nouell libertate vetus<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tus 
                cessare non debet: cui pug<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>nandum 
                est pro salute propria vel 
                <lb ed="#K"/>libertate communi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e164"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e167">31. epistola.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e166">Publicis de<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>bent 
              vtilitatibus insudare qui 
              <lb ed="#K"/>nomen dedere militie. quid 
              <lb ed="#K"/>enim agat homo si professo desit 
              <lb ed="#K"/>officio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e176"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e181">Libro 3. titulo 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e178">Diuitiarum secura 
              <lb ed="#K"/>non est possessio nisi armorum
              <lb ed="#K"/>defensione seruetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e186"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e193">10. titulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e188">Quis 
              <lb ed="#K"/>dubitat artem bellicam rebus
              <lb ed="#K"/>omnibus esse potiorem per quam li<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>bertas
              retinetur: et dignitas pro<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>uincie
              propagatur conseruatur imperium.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e198">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e209">Cassiodorus: epistolarum. libro i. epsitola 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e202">Animus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>ipse in audaciam non potest esse 
              <lb ed="#K"/>pronus qui diuersa cura fuerit 
              <lb ed="#K"/>sollicitus. Hanc merito expeditionem 
              <lb ed="#K"/>nominauere maiores: quia mens 
              <lb ed="#K"/>deuota preliis non debet aliis 
              <lb ed="#K"/>cogitationibus occupari. Constat
              <lb ed="#K"/>tempore necessitatis illum probari for<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tissimum 
              virum qui se per multa 
              <lb ed="#K"/>non distrahit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e221"> 
                <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e232">Libro 11. epistola 37.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e223">Sub 
                <lb ed="#K"/>incerta vita militia est.</quote>
            </p>
